On the rooftop where she'd climbed when all the laughter grew too [D7]loud 
And she [G]bowed and curtseyed to the man [C]who reached 
And offered her his [G]hand 
And [D7]led her down to the long white car that waited [G]past the crowd
{end_of_verse}

